<NomaiObject>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>1</ID>
		<Text>PLUME: Given concerns about our settlement’s stability, where should we construct a new, less temporary shelter?</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>2</ID>
		<ParentID>1</ParentID>
		<Text>THATCH: We need to stay close to the <![CDATA[<color=orange>escape pod</color>]]> so Filix can monitor incoming messages. We can’t be rescued if we aren’t present to respond.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>3</ID>
		<ParentID>2</ParentID>
		<Text>FILIX: I don’t believe anyone is coming to save us, Thatch. Now we must save ourselves.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>4</ID>
		<ParentID>3</ParentID>
		<Text>PLUME: I agree. We’re here because the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]>’s signal called to us and we followed. If we’re to find it, we need to not merely survive, but thrive.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>5</ID>
		<ParentID>1</ParentID>
		<Text>PLUME: I believe we should migrate to the northern glacier.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>6</ID>
		<ParentID>5</ParentID>
		<Text>FILIX: What if we use gravity crystals to craft a stable path?</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>7</ID>
		<ParentID>5</ParentID>
		<Text>THATCH: Building beneath the crust again would shelter us from the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>volcanic moon</color>]]>’s eruptions.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

	<TextBlock>
		<ID>8</ID>
		<ParentID>4</ParentID>
		<Text>THATCH: This is a wise point, Plume, and eloquently made. If moving to the northern glacier will keep us safer, then that is what we should do.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

